SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 928
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to commend Samara Young for exemplary
service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this General Assembly is pleased to recognize
certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment
of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Samara Young is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her
role as a legislative intern for Senator Jack Johnson; Ms. Young's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, a student at Lipscomb University, where she is highly regarded by her
peers, Ms. Young has achieved academic success while participating in numerous
extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Samara Young brought her many
abilities and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred
Fourteenth General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Ms. Young has surpassed all
criteria that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Samara Young has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight
and rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Samara Young for outstanding
SJR0928
